<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/wiki/en/index.php?title=Chennai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=48" title="Edit section: Drink">edit</a>][<a href="#Drink" title="click to add a drink listing" onclick="addListing(this, '48', 'drink', 'Chennai');">add listing</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Drink">Drink</span></h2>
<p>Chennai is a difficult place to drink. Government rule states that only establishments with a minimum of 21 rooms can obtain a bar/ liquor license. Hence there are no standalone bars or pubs here. All the bars hat are around are part of some hotel or the other and in general overpriced.
Government run liquor stores called TASMAC are all over the place but in general not at all a pleasant experience. They usually have rude staff, are filthy and usually never have the brand of your choice. Also they always tend to mark up each bottle by Rs 5 to 10 over the listed price. Go for it ifyou want a one time war like experience in order to obtain some booze!
</p><p>Nightclubs close at 23.00, even on fridays and saturdays, due to government rule. 
</p><p><br />
</p>
