<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/wiki/en/index.php?title=Chennai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=60" title="Edit section: Contact">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Contact">Contact</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/wiki/en/index.php?title=Chennai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=61" title="Edit section: Landlines">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Landlines">Landlines</span></h3>
<p><b>BSNL</b> <a href="http://chennai.bsnl.co.in" class="external autonumber" rel="nofollow">[97]</a> and <b>Airtel</b> <a href="http://www.airtel.in" class="external autonumber" rel="nofollow">[98]</a>  Reliance, Tata, are main providers of terrestrial telephone lines in Chennai. You can make <b>long distance calls</b> from one of the many booths that display NSD/ISD i.e. National Subscriber Dialling (National Long Distance) and International Subscriber Dialling (International Long Distance). Calling cards are also available with these providers which are considerably cheap.
</p>
